<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=144&amp;p=2118#p2118</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=144&amp;p=2118#p2118"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Diag trace]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=144&amp;p=2118#p2118"><![CDATA[
One simple solution is to build rom memory marking into an existing emulator such as FCEU and then to <br /><br />run the rom<br />set a starting point for rom memory marking<br />play the rom<br />stop the rom memory marking<br />dump the LIST of marked ares of the rom to a file<br /><br />This list of marked areas contains all of the <br />   a. data memory read from <br />   b. data memory written to<br />   c. instructions executed<br /><br />This way you could first:<br />  1. mark all code + data that is used in the startup screen<br /><br />  2. mark all code + data used in playing a particular part of the game.<p>Statistics: Posted by Guest — Thu May 19, 2005 9:47 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
